    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.18/37</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-02-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The President’s Message about
                    the Costa Rican Treaty came in yesterday afternoon. I had the former vote of
                    ratification reconsidered and the treaty was again ratified, as were also the
                    notes in the form suggested in the Message, so that there has been no loss of
                    time. I read over your letter of transmittal and find that it was my stupidity
                    which made me overlook the fact that you wanted the notes confirmed as well as
                    the treaty. I ought to have observed it but it is an unusual proceeding and,
                    although I noted your allusion to Portugal, I quite failed to observe that one
                    point.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. C. Lodge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
